The article is a transcript of remarks given by Vice President Mike Pence at the swearing-in ceremony of Carlos Trujillo as the 20th United States Ambassador to the Organization of American States. Pence expresses condolences for the crash of a Puerto Rico Air National Guard C-130 and welcomes Trujillo and his family. He highlights the importance of the Western Hemisphere to the United States and praises Trujillo's experience and leadership. Pence discusses the administration's priorities for the region, including trade relationships, security partnerships, and promoting freedom. Trujillo then takes the oath of office and delivers remarks expressing his gratitude and commitment to standing up for human rights and democracy.